div.div: Hiera extracts multi-scale features through four stages by progressively reducing spatial resolution and increasing channel dimensions. Early stages (high resolution) capture local details such as edges and textures, while later stages (low resolution) model global semantics such as objects and scenes.
In our experiments, we select features from the final stage.
